<seg id="13">The module & FSView; for & konqueror; provides a further view of objects with the MIME type inode / directory in local files. it can be used as an alternative for different symbol and text views to view the contents of your local file system.</seg>
<seg id="14">The peculiarity of & FSView; consists in visualising folder hierarchies with the help of a so-called Tree-Map. tree-Maps allow the representation of the size of objects in nested structures. this size must have the property that the sum of the sizes of the subordinate objects of an object is smaller or equal to the size of the object.</seg>
<seg id="15">"" "" "" "in this way, large files can be easily recognized even if they are located far below in the folder hierarchy. hence, & FSView; as a graphical and interactive version of the & UNIX command." "" "" ""</seg>
<seg id="16">In & FSView; an entry in the Treemap representation is a rectangle that represents a file or folder in your filesystem. for easier navigation use the rectangles useful color and labelling settings.</seg>
<seg id="17">"" "" "" "the color of a rectangle, which is switched from view color mode, can either display depth for easy detection of the nesting depth or the image of another file properties such as name, owner, group or MIME type." "" "" ""</seg>
<seg id="18">"" "" "" "a rectangle can be labeled with the different properties of the corresponding file or folder. for each property, you can specify whether there is sufficient space for displaying or whether the area of subordinate rectangles should be used. furthermore, you can specify the relative position of the label in the rectangle." "" "" ""</seg>
<seg id="19">"" "" "" "with Treemap in & FSView; frames are drawn to display the nesting of the entries, and these boxes need space that is not available for the frame when the rectangle is square." "" "" ""</seg>
<seg id="20">"" "" "" "how splitting the area of an entry for the subordinate entries is left to the implementation. in this case, the areas can be divided into columns, columns or recursive branches." "" "" ""</seg>
